{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887395411,"sessionID":"ses_284dd590dffefhhens6vGX3tL7","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2319c0001rVoENiSvFxMOGo","messageID":"msg_d7b22ca5e001Exa4dOlOvXgvzP","sessionID":"ses_284dd590dffefhhens6vGX3tL7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c4c6351e75f44279ad657402aa6709f1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-033/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-033/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-033 |\n8: | Module | root |\n9: | Language | Makefile |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: Establish a comprehensive Makefile build target system for AgentCube, providing:\n17: \n18: 1. **Build Standardization**: Unified build interface across all binaries (workloadmanager, router, picod, agentd, agentctl, agentcube, agentsandbox)\n19: 2. **Developer Ergonomics**: Short, memorable commands for common development tasks\n20: 3. **CI/CD Integration**: Consistent targets for GitHub Actions workflows\n21: 4. **Quality Gates**: Lint, test, coverage, and code generation verification targets\n22: 5. **Cross-Platform Support**: Multi-architecture build support with configurable variables\n23: \n24: **Target Categories**:\n25: \n26: | Category | Targets | Purpose |\n27: |----------|---------|---------|\n28: | Build | `build`, `build-*`, `all` | Compile Go binaries |\n29: | Test | `test`, `test-coverage`, `e2e`, `e2e-clean` | Run unit, coverage, and E2E tests |\n30: | Quality | `lint`, `fmt`, `gen-check`, `copyright-check` | Code quality verification |\n31: | Docker | `docker-build-*`, `docker-buildx-*` | Container image builds |\n32: | Install | `install`, `install-*` | Install binaries to `$GOPATH/bin` or custom prefix |\n33: | Clean | `clean`, `clean-*` | Remove build artifacts |\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n38: \n39: ### 2.1 In Scope\n40: \n41: | Deliverable | Description |\n42: |-------------|-------------|\n43: | `Makefile` rewrite | Comprehensive target system with categorized build targets |\n44: | Binary targets | Individual targets for each binary: `build-workloadmanager`, `build-router`, `build-picod`, `build-agentd`, `build-agentctl`, `build-agentcube`, `build-agentsandbox` |\n45: | Test targets | `test` (unit tests), `test-coverage` (coverage with html report), `test-race` (race detector) |\n46: | E2E targets | `e2e`, `e2e-setup`, `e2e-clean` for Kind-based end-to-end testing |\n47: | Quality targets | `lint` (golangci-lint), `fmt` (go fmt), `vet` (go vet), `gen-check` (codegen verification) |\n48: | Install targets | `install` (all binaries), `install-workloadmanager`, etc. |\n49: | Docker targets | Preserve existing `docker-build-*`, `docker-buildx-*` targets |\n50: | Cross-compile targets | `build-linux-amd64`, `build-linux-arm64`, `build-darwin-amd64`, etc. |\n51: | Help target | `make help` with formatted target documentation |\n52: \n53: ### 2.2 Binary Inventory\n54: \n55: | Binary | Source Path | Output | Description |\n56: |--------|-------------|--------|-------------|\n57: | `workloadmanager` | `./cmd/workloadmanager` | `bin/workloadmanager` | Workload manager HTTP server |\n58: | `router` | `./cmd/router` | `bin/router` | Session routing and reverse proxy |\n59: | `picod` | `./cmd/picod` | `bin/picod` | Local code execution daemon |\n60: | `agentd` | `./cmd/agentd` | `bin/agentd` | Idle cleanup controller |\n61: | `agentctl` | `./cmd/agentctl` | `bin/agentctl` | CLI tool for AgentCube |\n62: | `agentcube` | `./cmd/agentcube` | `bin/agentcube` | Main CLI binary |\n63: | `agentsandbox` | `./cmd/agentsandbox` | `bin/agentsandbox` | Sandbox management binary |\n64: \n65: ### 2.3 Variable System\n66: \n67: | Variable | Default | Description |\n68: |----------|---------|-------------|\n69: | `IMAGE_REPO` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube` | Docker image repository |\n70: | `VERSION` | `git describe --tags --always --dirty` | Version tag for images |\n71: | `TARGETOS` | `linux` | Target OS for cross-compilation |\n72: | `TARGETARCH` | `amd64` | Target architecture |\n73: | `GO_VERSION` | `1.24` | Go version for CI alignment |\n74: | `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` | `1.64.7` | golangci-lint version |\n75: | `BINDIR` | `bin/` | Output directory for binaries |\n76: | `INSTALL_PREFIX` | `$GOPATH/bin` | Installation prefix |\n77: \n78: ### 2.4 Out of Scope\n79: \n80: | Item | Reason |\n81: |------|--------|\n82: | Python SDK targets | Python has separate `pyproject.toml` and `pytest` setup |\n83: | Helm chart targets | Covered by separate Helm tooling |\n84: | Release automation | Covered by `build-push-release.yml` workflow |\n85: | Makefile documentation beyond `help` target | External documentation in `docs/` |\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n90: \n91: ### 3.1 新增文件\n92: \n93: | File | Description |\n94: |------|-------------|\n95: | N/A | No new files; Makefile will be enhanced |\n96: \n97: ### 3.2 修改文件\n98: \n99: | File | Change |\n100: |------|--------|\n101: | `Makefile` | Major rewrite: add categorized targets, help system, cross-compile support |\n102: | `.github/workflows/*.yml` | Update to use new Make targets (e.g., `make lint` instead of inline commands) |\n103: \n104: ### 3.3 Target Mapping (Current → New)\n105: \n106: | Current Target | New Target | Notes |\n107: |----------------|------------|-------|\n108: | `all` | `all` | Unchanged; depends on `build` |\n109: | `build` | `build` | Enhanced; builds all binaries |\n110: | N/A | `build-workloadmanager` | New single binary target |\n111: | N/A | `build-router` | New single binary target |\n112: | N/A | `build-picod` | New single binary target |\n113: | N/A | `build-agentd` | New single binary target |\n114: | `test` | `test` | Enhanced with verbose flag |\n115: | N/A | `test-coverage` | New coverage target |\n116: | N/A | `test-race` | New race detector target |\n117: | N/A | `e2e`, `e2e-clean` | New E2E test targets |\n118: | N/A | `lint` | New golangci-lint target |\n119: | N/A | `fmt`, `vet` | New formatting targets |\n120: | N/A | `gen-check` | New codegen verification target |\n121: | `docker-build` | `docker-build` | Unchanged |\n122: | `docker-build-router` | `docker-build-router` | Unchanged |\n123: | `docker-build-picod` | `docker-build-picod` | Unchanged |\n124: | `docker-build-all` | `docker-build-all` | Unchanged |\n125: | `docker-buildx-*` | `docker-buildx-*` | Unchanged |\n126: | `clean` | `clean` | Enhanced; cleans all artifacts |\n127: | N/A | `install`, `install-*` | New installation targets |\n128: | N/A | `help` | New help target |\n129: \n130: ### 3.4 Upstream Dependencies\n131: \n132: | Dependency | Purpose |\n133: |------------|---------|\n134: | `go` | Go toolchain (1.24+) |\n135: | `golangci-lint` | Linting tool |\n136: | `docker` | Container builds |\n137: | `docker buildx` | Multi-arch builds |\n138: | `kind` | E2E testing cluster |\n139: | `helm` | E2E chart deployment |\n140: | `git` | Version tagging |\n141: \n142: ### 3.5 Downstream Consumers\n143: \n144: | Consumer | Usage |\n145: |----------|-------|\n146: | `CI: main.yml` | `make build` for build verification |\n147: | `CI: lint.yml` | `make lint` for golangci-lint |\n148: | `CI: test-coverage.yml` | `make test-coverage` for coverage |\n149: | `CI: e2e.yml` | `make e2e`, `make e2e-clean` |\n150: | `CI: codegen-check.yml` | `make gen-check` |\n151: | `CI: copyright-check.yml` | `make gen-copyright` |\n152: | `CI: build-push-release.yml` | `make docker-buildx-push-*` |\n153: | `E2E: run_e2e.sh` | `make docker-build`, `make docker-build-router`, `make docker-build-picod` |\n154: | Developers | `make help`, `make build`, `make test`, `make lint` |\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n159: \n160: ### Alternative 1: Separate Makefiles per Component\n161: \n162: **Approach**: Create `Makefile` in each `cmd/` subdirectory.\n163: \n164: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n165: |--------|------------|\n166: | Pros | Component isolation; independent builds |\n167: | Cons | Duplication; harder to manage cross-cutting concerns (lint, coverage); CI complexity |\n168: \n169: **Decision**: Rejected. Single root Makefile provides unified interface and simpler CI configuration.\n170: \n171: ### Alternative 2: Just/Task/Earthly instead of Make\n172: \n173: **Approach**: Use modern task runners (Just, Task, Earthly) instead of GNU Make.\n174: \n175: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n176: |--------|------------|\n177: | Pros | Modern syntax; better dependency management; Earthly provides containerized builds |\n178: | Cons | Additional tool dependency; team unfamiliarity; CI requires installation; GNU Make is ubiquitous |\n179: \n180: **Decision**: Rejected. GNU Make is universally available in CI environments and familiar to all developers.\n181: \n182: ### Alternative 3: Shell Scripts for Complex Operations\n183: \n184: **Approach**: Keep Makefile minimal; use shell scripts for complex operations (E2E, codegen).\n185: \n186: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n187: |--------|------------|\n188: | Pros | More programming flexibility; easier conditionals |\n189: | Cons | Multiple entry points; `make help` cannot document scripts; harder to maintain consistency |\n190: \n191: **Decision**: Partially adopted. E2E test script `run_e2e.sh` preserved; Makefile targets wrap the script for unified interface.\n192: \n193: ### Alternative 4: No Cross-Compile Targets\n194: \n195: **Approach**: Rely solely on Docker buildx for multi-arch builds; no native cross-compile targets.\n196: \n197: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n198: |--------|------------|\n199: | Pros | Simpler Makefile; Docker handles cross-compilation |\n200: | Cons | Slower iteration for cross-arch development; cannot test binaries without Docker |\n201: \n202: **Decision**: Rejected. Native cross-compile targets (`build-linux-arm64`, etc.) enable fast local testing without Docker overhead.\n203: \n204: ### Alternative 5: Bazel/Buck Build System\n205: \n206: **Approach**: Adopt Bazel or Buck for hermetic, reproducible builds.\n207: \n208: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n209: |--------|------------|\n210: | Pros | Deterministic builds; remote caching; advanced dependency management |\n211: | Cons | Significant migration effort; steep learning curve; overkill for current project scale |\n212: \n213: **Decision**: Rejected. Makefile + Go modules provides sufficient build reproducibility at current project scale.\n214: \n215: ---\n216: \n217: ## 5. Risks\n218: \n219: | Risk | Mitigation |\n220: |------|------------|\n221: | Makefile complexity growth | Organize targets by category; use `make help` for discoverability; document in comments |\n222: | Target naming inconsistency | Follow Go community conventions; use `kebab-case` for multi-word targets |\n223: | CI workflow divergence | CI workflows must reference Make targets, not inline commands |\n224: | Version drift between CI and Makefile | Use shared variables (`GO_VERSION`, `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION`); document in comments |\n225: | Race conditions in parallel builds | Use `.NOTPARALLEL` for sensitive targets; ensure `go build` handles parallelism |\n226: | Hidden dependencies | Use phony targets with explicit dependencies; document prerequisites |\n227: \n228: ---\n229: \n230: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n231: \n232: - [ ] Add binary-specific build targets (`build-workloadmanager`, `build-router`, etc.)\n233: - [ ] Add `test-coverage` target with html report output\n234: - [ ] Add `test-race` target with race detector enabled\n235: - [ ] Add `lint` target using golangci-lint\n236: - [ ] Add `fmt` and `vet` targets\n237: - [ ] Add `gen-check` target for codegen verification\n238: - [ ] Add `gen-copyright` target for copyright headers\n239: - [ ] Add `e2e` and `e2e-clean` targets wrapping `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`\n240: - [ ] Add `install` and `install-*` targets\n241: - [ ] Add cross-compile targets (`build-linux-amd64`, `build-linux-arm64`, etc.)\n242: - [ ] Add `help` target with formatted output\n243: - [ ] Organize targets into logical categories with comments\n244: - [ ] Update `.PHONY` declarations\n245: - [ ] Document variables with `?=` defaults\n246: - [ ] Verify CI workflows reference new targets\n247: - [ ] Test `make help` output is readable\n248: - [ ] Test all targets work on Linux and macOS\n249: \n250: ---\n251: \n252: ## 7. References\n253: \n254: - GNU Make Manual: https://www.gnu.org/software/make/manual/\n255: - Go Build Modes: https://go.dev/cmd/go/#hdr-Build_modes\n256: - golangci-lint: https://golangci-lint.run/\n257: - Kind (Kubernetes in Docker): https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/\n258: - GitHub Actions Makefile best practices: https://docs.github.com/en/actions/using-workflows/workflow-syntax-for-github-actions#jobsjob_idstepsshell\n259: - ci-cd/design.md — Existing workflow targets (lines 8-20)\n260: - deployment/design.md — Docker build targets\n261: - test/e2e/run_e2e.sh — E2E test orchestration\n\n(End of file - total 261 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-033 |\n| Module | root |\n| Language | Makefile |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nEstablish a comprehensive Makefile build target system for AgentCube, providing:\n\n1. **Build Standardization**: Unified build interface across all binaries (workloadmanager, router, picod, agentd, agentctl, agentcube, agentsandbox)\n2. **Developer Ergonomics**: Short, memorable commands for common development tasks\n3. **CI/CD Integration**: Consistent targets for GitHub Actions workflows","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-033/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775887395380,"end":1775887395410}}}}
